QUESTION NO: 1
Your company network includes Microsoft Exchange Server 2007 and Forefront Protection for
Exchange Server (FPE) 2010 in a Windows Server 2008 environment. You discover unknown
malware (malicious software) that has infected some mailboxes. You view the FPE console. You
do not see a notification regarding the malware infection. You need to immediately scan specific
mailboxes. Which type of scan should you run?
A. On-Demand
B. Scheduled
C. Transport
D. Real time
Answer: A

QUESTION NO: 2
Your company network includes Microsoft Exchange Server 2010 and Forefront Protection for
Exchange Server (FPE) 2010 in a Windows Server 2008 environment. You need to enable spam
filtering in FPE by using the Forefront Management Shell. Which Forefront Management Shell
cmdlet should you use?
A. Set-FseSpamConnectionFilter
B. Set-FseSpamContentFilter
C. Set-FseSpamFiltering
D. Set-FseFilterList
Answer: C
